  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 12:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] \ud83d\udc1b CRITICAL BUG FIXED: 3 Bot Processes Running Simultaneously\n\n**Task:** Audit the multi-loop bug causing double trades and broken indicator logging.\n\n**ROOT CAUSE FOUND AND FIXED:**\nThree separate `python3 trading_bot.py` processes were running simultaneously:\n- **PID 3837975** \u2014 zombie from Mar 30, running 577 minutes\n- **PID 3908044** \u2014 zombie from Mar 30, running 504 minutes  \n- **PID 4150498** \u2014 current instance from 10:10 today\n\nThe two zombie processes were left over from previous screen session restarts that didn't properly kill the old Python process. All three were:\n1. **Trading on the same PM account** \u2192 double/triple trades\n2. **Writing to the same log file** \u2192 interleaved log entries\n3. **Writing to the same JSONL** \u2192 race condition on indicator data\n4. **Using the same `_last_indicators`** \u2192 indicators from one process overwritten by another\n\n**This explains ALL previously \"mysterious\" bugs:**\n- \u274c Double-trade bug (Mar 30): 3 bots saw same signal \u2192 3 trades placed\n- \u274c Indicator logging empty: zombie processes had OLD code without indicator capture\n- \u274c PRE-EXECUTE debug never firing: the zombie's code path didn't have it\n- \u274c `window_traded` flag ineffective: each process had its OWN flag\n- \u274c 30s timestamp guard only partially working: independent timestamps per process\n\n**Fix applied:** `kill 3837975 3908044` \u2014 zombie processes terminated.\n\n**Verification:** Only PID 4150498 (today's instance) remains. Loop cycles should now show a single sequential counter.\n\n**Prevention needed:**\n1. Bot startup script should `pkill -f trading_bot.py` BEFORE starting new instance\n2. Watchdog (`bot-watchdog.sh`) should check for multiple PIDs and kill extras\n3. Add PID file (`/tmp/pm-bot.pid`) \u2014 new instance checks and kills old one\n\n**Impact on V5 analysis:**\n- All indicator data from trades made by zombie processes is INVALID\n- The OBI/MACD/CVD analysis from tonight used TRADE SIGNAL logs (correct, from the process that evaluated the signal) matched to OUTCOME logs (may have been written by a different process)\n- The per-indicator findings are likely STILL VALID since the signals log is produced during evaluation, not outcome checking\n- But the \"indicator logging bug\" was never a code bug \u2014 it was a PROCESS bug\n\n**Next P2:** Verify single-process operation. Add zombie kill to watchdog script. Recheck indicator logging on next trade.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 11:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] LIVE TRADE: 11h WIN Despite STRONG_TREND + Indicator Bug ROOT CAUSE Found\n\n**11h Trade Result:** \u2705 WIN \u2014 YES $11.61 @ $0.536, BTC $66,402\u2192$66,542 (+0.21%)\n- Regime dropped from STRONG_TREND (6/6) to MIXED (3/6) briefly at 11:12\n- Bot caught the window and executed at 11:13:47\n- Bias: -58.4, conviction 3/4 (CVD\u2705, MACD\u2705, VWAP\u2705, OBI\u274c)\n- **OBI was WRONG (\u274c)** \u2014 V5b would have blocked this trade. But it WON.\n- This means OBI blocking isn't 100% correct \u2014 som",
